  {"id":"ped-reflujo-gastro","nombreEs":"Reflujo Gastroesofagico en Lactantes","nombreEn":"Gastroesophageal Reflux in Infants","categoriaEs":"Gastrointestinal","categoriaEn":"Gastrointestinal","edadAplicable":"0-12 meses","descripcionEs":"Regurgitacion del contenido gastrico hacia el esofago, extremadamente comun en lactantes. El reflujo fisiologico (bebe feliz que escupe) se distingue de la enfermedad por reflujo que causa sintomas significativos.","descripcionEn":"Regurgitation of gastric contents into the esophagus, extremely common in infants. Physiological reflux (happy spitter) is distinguished from reflux disease causing significant symptoms.","sintomasEs":["Regurgitaciones frecuentes despues de comer","Arqueo de espalda durante o despues de alimentarse","Irritabilidad durante las tomas","Rechazo del alimento","Tos o atragantamiento con las tomas","Pobre ganancia de peso (en enfermedad por reflujo)"],"sintomasEn":["Frequent regurgitation after feeding","Back arching during or after feeding","Irritability during feeds","Food refusal","Coughing or choking with feeds","Poor weight gain (in reflux disease)"],"tratamientoEnCasaEs":["Alimentar en posicion mas vertical","Tomas mas pequenas y mas frecuentes","Eructar al bebe cada 2-3 onzas","Mantener erguido 20-30 min despues de comer","Elevar cabecera de la cuna ligeramente","Espesar formula si el pediatra lo recomienda","Evitar ropa apretada en abdomen"],"tratamientoEnCasaEn":["Feed in more upright position","Smaller, more frequent feeds","Burp baby every 2-3 ounces","Keep upright 20-30 min after feeding","Slightly elevate head of crib","Thicken formula if pediatrician recommends","Avoid tight clothing on abdomen"],"cuandoIrAlMedicoEs":["Regurgitacion que aumenta en frecuencia o volumen","Irritabilidad excesiva con las tomas","Pobre ganancia de peso","Sintomas mas alla de los 12 meses","Necesidad de cambio de formula"],"cuandoIrAlMedicoEn":["Regurgitation increasing in frequency or volume","Excessive irritability with feeds","Poor weight gain","Symptoms beyond 12 months","Need for formula change"],"cuandoIrAUrgenciasEs":["Vomito verde (bilioso) — puede indicar obstruccion","Vomito con sangre","Rechazo total de alimentacion con deshidratacion","Perdida de peso documentada","Eventos de apnea o cianosis"],"cuandoIrAUrgenciasEn":["Green (bilious) vomiting — may indicate obstruction","Bloody vomit","Complete food refusal with dehydration","Documented weight loss","Apnea or cyanosis events"],"prevencionEs":["Tecnica de alimentacion adecuada","Posicion correcta durante y despues de tomas","No sobrealimentar","Lactancia materna puede reducir severidad"],"prevencionEn":["Proper feeding technique","Correct position during and after feeds","Do not overfeed","Breastfeeding may reduce severity"],"datosImportantesEs":["El 50% de bebes regurgitan diariamente a los 2-4 meses","El 95% resuelve espontaneamente antes de los 12-18 meses","La mayoria NO necesita medicacion","El vomito bilioso (verde) siempre requiere evaluacion urgente","La cirugia (funduplicatura) se reserva para casos severos refractarios"],"datosImportantesEn":["50% of babies spit up daily at 2-4 months","95% resolves spontaneously before 12-18 months","Most do NOT need medication","Bilious (green) vomiting always requires urgent evaluation","Surgery (fundoplication) reserved for severe refractory cases"],"contagioso":false},
  {"id":"ped-impetigo","nombreEs":"Impetigo","nombreEn":"Impetigo","categoriaEs":"Dermatologia / Infecciosa","categoriaEn":"Dermatology / Infectious","edadAplicable":"2-6 anos","descripcionEs":"Infeccion bacteriana superficial de la piel causada por Staphylococcus aureus o Streptococcus pyogenes. Es la infeccion cutanea bacteriana mas comun en ninos. Altamente contagiosa por contacto directo.","descripcionEn":"Superficial bacterial skin infection caused by Staphylococcus aureus or Streptococcus pyogenes. It is the most common bacterial skin infection in children. Highly contagious through direct contact.","sintomasEs":["Vesiculas que se rompen y forman costras amarillas (color miel)","Lesiones que se extienden por auto-inoculacion (rascado)","Generalmente en cara (alrededor de nariz y boca)","Picor leve a moderado","Ganglios locales pueden estar inflamados","Forma ampollosa: ampollas grandes con liquido claro"],"sintomasEn":["Vesicles that break and form yellow (honey-colored) crusts","Lesions spreading by self-inoculation (scratching)","Usually on face (around nose and mouth)","Mild to moderate itching","Local lymph nodes may be swollen","Bullous form: large blisters with clear fluid"],"tratamientoEnCasaEs":["Antibiotico topico (mupirocina) para casos leves","Lavar lesiones suavemente con agua y jabon","Cubrir lesiones con gasa para prevenir contagio","Cortar unas y evitar rascado","Lavar ropa, toallas y sabanas diariamente","No compartir articulos personales"],"tratamientoEnCasaEn":["Topical antibiotic (mupirocin) for mild cases","Gently wash lesions with soap and water","Cover lesions with gauze to prevent spread","Trim nails and avoid scratching","Wash clothes, towels, and sheets daily","Do not share personal items"],"cuandoIrAlMedicoEs":["Lesiones que se extienden a pesar de tratamiento topico","Multiples areas afectadas","Fiebre asociada","Lesiones cerca de los ojos","No mejora tras 3 dias de antibiotico topico"],"cuandoIrAlMedicoEn":["Lesions spreading despite topical treatment","Multiple areas affected","Associated fever","Lesions near eyes","No improvement after 3 days of topical antibiotic"],"cuandoIrAUrgenciasEs":["Celulitis: enrojecimiento profundo, calor y dolor extenso","Fiebre alta con lesiones extensas","Orina oscura (posible glomerulonefritis post-estreptococica)"],"cuandoIrAUrgenciasEn":["Cellulitis: deep redness, warmth, and extensive pain","High fever with extensive lesions","Dark urine (possible post-streptococcal glomerulonephritis)"],"prevencionEs":["Higiene adecuada y lavado de manos","Tratar raspones y picaduras de insectos pronto","No compartir toallas ni ropa","Mantener unas cortas y limpias","Nino puede volver a la escuela 24h despues de iniciar antibiotico"],"prevencionEn":["Proper hygiene and handwashing","Treat scrapes and insect bites promptly","Do not share towels or clothing","Keep nails short and clean","Child can return to school 24h after starting antibiotic"],"datosImportantesEs":["Es la infeccion cutanea mas comun en ninos de 2-6 anos","El tratamiento topico es suficiente para casos leves y localizados","Antibioticos orales se necesitan si hay multiples lesiones o formas ampollosas","Puede complicarse con glomerulonefritis post-estreptococica (raro)","El MRSA comunitario es una causa creciente"],"datosImportantesEn":["Most common skin infection in children aged 2-6","Topical treatment sufficient for mild, localized cases","Oral antibiotics needed for multiple lesions or bullous forms","Can be complicated by post-streptococcal glomerulonephritis (rare)","Community MRSA is an increasing cause"],"contagioso":true,"vacunaDisponible":false}
